article.headline: Bowling Green 67, Ball St. 57
article.story: BOWLING GREEN, Ohio (AP) -- Martin Samarco scored 21 points to lead Bowling Green to a 67-57 win over Ball State on Wednesday night. Brian Moten added 16 points and Nate Miller had 15 points and nine rebounds for the Falcons (11-10, 2-6 Mid-American Conference), who took a 36-25 lead at halftime. Bowling Green led by as much as 12 points in the second half. Anthony Newell led Ball State (7-14, 3-5) with 13 points and 14 rebounds and was the only Cardinals player to reach double digits in either. The Cardinals shot 34 percent (16-of-47), compared with Bowling Green's 44 percent (20-of-45). Ball State outrebounded the Falcons 36-28. Bowling Green scored 19 points off 16 Cardinals turnovers.
